==English==

===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] US [ˈhoʊmi]

===Etymology===
Shortened form of [[homeboy]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}  {{slang}}

# Someone, particularly a male acquaintance, from one's hometown.
# A close friend or fellow member of a youth gang.
#:''Hey there, Alex, my '''homey'''!''
# An inner-city youth.

===Usage notes===
Very informal slang associated with urban [[w:African-American Vernacular English|African-American Vernacular English]].

